 a big clue here.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031185,0.069099,0.086568,0.093428,0.093605,0.090882,0.092722,0.090917,0.090054,0.096038,0.084755,0.080747],"unified_progress":[0.043493,0.063383,0.074162,0.086301,0.090747,0.092932,0.094486,0.095517,0.095622,0.099384,0.089643,0.074331]},{"section":15,"text":"Other possibilities could be aortic dissection or another cause of hemorrhage, but the GI bleed seems more likely given the symptoms and meds.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025979,0.062105,0.079134,0.088076,0.092143,0.09385,0.097921,0.097763,0.097255,0.097215,0.089378,0.079182],"unified_progress":[0.028281,0.056355,0.071277,0.08267,0.090109,0.094062,0.098055,0.10095,0.10259,0.10535,0.094249,0.076055]},{"section":16,"text":"So putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is an upper gastrointestinal bleed, probably from a peptic ulcer caused by aspirin.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034868,0.065113,0.074343,0.08117,0.084446,0.086421,0.089209,0.089383,0.092319,0.093361,0.092374,0.11699],"unified_progress":[0.038472,0.048427,0.059708,0.07106,0.076609,0.084171,0.087884,0.092573,0.098065,0.10073,0.11294,0.12936]},{"section":17,"text":"The patient's medications (aspirin especially) are a major risk factor.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032239,0.065246,0.07709,0.08453,0.09026,0.096335,0.095963,0.095983,0.094521,0.096375,0.088833,0.082624],"unified_progress":[0.065642,0.083804,0.078047,0.077324,0.080073,0.084359,0.085101,0.091497,0.090389,0.091619,0.090031,0.082113]},{"section":18,"text":"The hypotension and tachycardia are signs of hemorrhage.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022653,0.052701,0.066383,0.078512,0.090152,0.097935,0.10495,0.10356,0.10141,0.099223,0.096978,0.085539],"unified_progress":[0.040418,0.048603,0.060809,0.066638,0.08083,0.090407,0.094986,0.10071,0.10601,0.11022,0.10874,0.09163]},{"section":19,"text":"I don't think it's a myocardial infarction because the presentation is more about bleeding, but his history of CAD is there.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025669,0.056962,0.069437,0.078824,0.086517,0.09344,0.09966,0.1025,0.10301,0.10222,0.096824,0.084942],"unified_progress":[0.034945,0.057018,0.066318,0.074036,0.083622,0.089882,0.094636,0.10109,0.10388,0.10944,0.10309,0.082041]},{"section":20,"text":"However, the key symptoms point to GI bleed.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023431,0.054114,0.069664,0.07891,0.085101,0.089183,0.095952,0.098541,0.1005,0.10388,0.10064,0.10008],"unified_progress":[0.031427,0.050408,0.061615,0.071687,0.079729,0.085697,0.093022,0.098734,0.10264,0.11096,0.10994,0.10414]}]}}